# LeadFlow Coding Rules

- Use TypeScript everywhere (strict mode enabled).
- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling, following modern UI/UX best practices (harmony, dark mode support, glassmorphism, smooth animations).
- Use Zod for all input validation (API schemas, forms, environmental variables).
- Commit incrementally with clear, descriptive semantic commit messages.
- Maintain documentation integrity: do not remove comments or docstrings unless requested.
- Outbound email sending is sensitive: run in review-driven mode, never auto-execute real sends during testing.
